article.headline: Old Dominion 63, Duquesne 54
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Gerald Lee was the lone player in double figures for Old Dominion, scoring 24 points to lead the Monarchs in a 63-54 win over Duquesne on Wednesday night. Lee, who finished 10-for-18 from the floor, also chipped in with six rebounds and three blocks. The Monarchs (9-4) totaled 12 blocks, and Frank Hassell led the way with four. Keyon Carter grabbed nine boards for Old Dominion, which leads the all-time series 5-1. The teams stayed close throughout the first half, but the Monarchs ended the frame on a 5-0 run for a 28-23 going into the break. Up just three points early in the second, the Monarchs put together a 7-2 run to give them a 10-point cushion with less than 17 minutes left and led the rest of the way. Sean Johnson led the Dukes (9-5) with 17 points. The Monarchs have won three straight games and five of their last six.
